42 (1) The number of students who qualified for automatic enrollment in the advanced
43 mathematics pathway and were automatically enrolled in the advanced mathematics
44 pathway;
45 (2) The number of students who qualified for automatic enrollment in the advanced
46 mathematics pathway and opted out of such automatic enrollment;
47 (3) The number of students who did not qualify for automatic enrollment and enrolled
48 in the advanced mathematics pathway;
49 (4) A list of courses offered as part of the advanced mathematics pathway and any
50 related services or supports offered to students; and
51 (5) The scores on the end-of-grade assessment in mathematics for each category of
52 students listed in paragraphs (1) through (3) of this subsection."
53 SECTION 2.
54 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
